abid.title: There should be a workflow to change the AbID prefix for an existing AbID when it changes size

comments.body:
Discussion:

workflow for Marc AbID
- An abid is an absolute identifier, that designates a spot on the shelf. E.g. if it’s Q01 it’s the first thing in the Q section.
- They bring 30 books to the office that have already been cataloged in Alma and they already have barcodes in them.
- They say “it’s folio”
- they scan all 36 in order.
- the app generates an AbID for each of them. They are sequential.
- Synchronizing means it gets put in a field in the Alma record.
- New use case: I had a folder. someone pulled it out and put it in a box. Now it’s not a folder anymore. It has the same barcode because it’s the same item.
- Need a button that lets you set a new prefix
- the default interface is aspace, and there’s also a button for Marc batches.
  - this feature is behind the “marc batches” button.
- Question: Is abid-staging hooked to staging instances of aspace and alma?
  - probably, but not entirely sure.

bibdata.title: Add mermaid chart about SCSB full re-indexing process
Running the full SCSB reindex it's indexing old daily scsb updates.

comments.body: I believe this happened because the most recent full dump in prod (ID 4309), while it has a created_at of January 13th, has a generated_date of January 1.  Compared to 4309, incremental 4271 has a created_at of January 6, so it seems like an old update to us.  However, its generated_date is January 5, so the rake task considers it to be more recent than the full dump.

@christinach and I looked at this today.  The generated_date of January 1 is expected (this is when PUL requested the dump via the SCSB API).  This does not explain the very old incrementals (e.g. from 2 years ago) that were being indexed before.  However, since those incrementals have been deleted now, we'll close this issue for now, and troubleshoot further if it happens again.
